WEBVTT

00:00.226 --> 00:03.190
Again, Merry Christmas.

00:04.291 --> 00:11.861
Our text for our meditation this morning comes to us from our gospel lesson in John and a little bit of our Old Testament lesson as well.

00:13.243 --> 00:14.184
Let's begin with prayer.

00:16.747 --> 00:28.242
Dear Lord Heavenly Father, we just sang it upon our frail humanity, your finger chose to trace the fullness of your deity, the icon of your grace.

00:29.090 --> 00:44.913
We thank you for the gift that we receive this morning, the gift of your son, the gift of your son, Jesus, who will restore us, who will give us eternal life, who we receive daily the food of his word, and today receive the food in his Lord's Supper.

00:45.795 --> 00:58.994
We just ask now that by the power of your Holy Spirit present among us that you would plant your word deep within us that it would guide us, guide our thoughts and our actions, and let everyone see the light of Christ in us in our daily lives, in the name of Jesus we pray.

00:59.330 --> 00:59.691
Amen.

01:01.453 --> 01:02.134
Please be seated.

01:07.403 --> 01:13.172
Dear brothers and sisters in Christ here at Mount Calvary, what a joyous day this is.

01:14.213 --> 01:19.702
For us, for you, as we celebrate the birth of our Savior Jesus Christ.

01:21.545 --> 01:27.474
And as we gather in the beauty of this sanctuary, God's house, surrounded by

01:28.194 --> 01:29.315
Beautiful stained glass.

01:29.535 --> 01:31.998
Yeah, I wish there was a Christmas one in there, but there's not.

01:34.120 --> 01:42.427
Surrounded by stained glass, beautiful soaring architecture, the beautiful decorations, the music, the carols, and the hymns of the season.

01:44.149 --> 01:49.714
I think it's good for us to pause and let what's happening here sink in a little bit.

01:51.956 --> 01:55.500
God didn't send us a memo from heaven.

01:55.820 --> 01:57.842
He didn't send us some unrecognized

01:58.050 --> 02:06.060
Unrecognizable being, he didn't send a distant thunderclap of judgment to the world.

02:06.120 --> 02:14.571
But he came down himself as a baby, recognizable.

02:16.153 --> 02:21.319
One of us, wrapped in swaddling clothes lying in a manger.

02:24.042 --> 02:26.866
And today on this holy

02:26.978 --> 02:31.423
Christmas morning, and we received the holiness of God in this little baby.

02:31.443 --> 02:38.871
Our gospel reading from John 1 invites us kind of into the heart of all of this.

02:39.712 --> 02:48.883
And I don't know about you, but John 1 is one of those readings where every time I read that first opening passages that we had this morning, it kind of gives me the chills.

02:48.983 --> 02:55.250
It gives me that assurance of my faith, that God

02:55.586 --> 03:05.500
has been here, that Jesus has been here, that they have been here since creation, and it has a beautiful way of taking creation and this day and wrapping it all together.

03:05.520 --> 03:15.894
And the kernel that I love in that chapter is, and the word became flesh and dwelt among us.

03:17.136 --> 03:24.466
And we have seen his glory, glory as of the only Son from the Father, full of grace and truth.

03:26.594 --> 03:30.279
I like to put myself in a place of people in scripture because they were.

03:30.319 --> 03:31.961
They were just like you and me.

03:33.383 --> 03:45.879
And so it's easy for us for a many way to imagine myself as kind of a regular little slunk shepherd on the hills of Bethlehem that night, the night's ordinary.

03:46.079 --> 03:48.582
Maybe it's a little cool, quiet routine.

03:48.642 --> 03:51.666
And then suddenly,

03:52.418 --> 03:57.203
Angel shattered the darkness with this glory and this beautiful good news.

03:59.386 --> 04:13.742
Or picture Mary and Joseph exhausted from traveling, holding their newborn son, not really knowing who he was, that somehow he is the eternal God in this little baby.

04:13.782 --> 04:21.330
Imagine all of that happening to ordinary people.

04:23.330 --> 04:31.941
And Christmas isn't kind of what we make it here, kind of this cozy holiday with the decorations and gifts and everything.

04:31.961 --> 04:44.197
When you think about it, it's the invasion for John 1 of divine light into our darkened and shadowed world.

04:46.220 --> 04:47.922
And that should make us all smile.

04:51.426 --> 04:53.208
And that's why I love about John's gospel.

04:53.388 --> 04:56.952
It doesn't start with shepherds or wise men or camels or any of that.

04:58.174 --> 05:01.217
It begins with eternity.

05:02.399 --> 05:03.540
It begins with creation.

05:03.580 --> 05:05.122
In the beginning was the word.

05:07.585 --> 05:14.813
And then the miracle that we celebrate this morning and that word became flesh.

05:17.817 --> 05:18.898
Not some

05:19.394 --> 05:31.388
extraordinary superhero type of being, descending in power and fanfare for the baby, vulnerable and human.

05:34.811 --> 05:35.072
Why?

05:35.112 --> 05:43.982
Because God wanted to dwell among us, to pitch his tent in our midst.

05:45.864 --> 05:47.826
And the Greek, it suggests that

05:47.938 --> 05:49.340
He tabernacles with us.

05:51.624 --> 05:54.829
We've seen his glory, John says, full of grace and truth.

05:57.293 --> 06:03.823
And then the past few weeks we've talked about how that holiness of God, especially to his Old Testament, people could be quite a terrifying thing.

06:06.688 --> 06:08.270
In the Old Testament, God was.

06:08.330 --> 06:10.053
God's glory was terrifying.

06:10.133 --> 06:15.602
Moses on Sinai hidden in the rock because no one could see God's face and live.

06:17.698 --> 06:22.124
and these beautiful prophecies that we've been marching through this advent in Isaiah.

06:23.686 --> 06:33.579
Isaiah prophesies the day when that would all change, that there would be no longer terror when we came face to face with our God.

06:37.984 --> 06:39.346
Isaiah said it in his

06:39.618 --> 06:42.981
one of his prophecies that we would verse into songs of joy together.

06:43.402 --> 06:44.783
And we talk about Jerusalem.

06:44.823 --> 06:47.966
You verse into songs of joy together, you ruins of Jerusalem.

06:48.006 --> 06:49.988
For the Lord has comforted his people.

06:50.028 --> 06:51.870
He has redeemed Jerusalem.

06:52.250 --> 06:57.115
The Lord will bear his holy arm in the sight of all the nations and all the ends of the earth.

06:57.195 --> 07:06.725
We'll see the salvation of our God in a little tiny day being.

07:06.765 --> 07:07.986
Isaiah 52,

07:08.066 --> 07:12.873
Our Old Testament lesson paints a picture kind of of a ruined city.

07:14.956 --> 07:16.438
Jerusalem in exile.

07:18.762 --> 07:19.763
Broken by sin.

07:21.186 --> 07:22.227
Broken by oppression.

07:24.691 --> 07:27.575
A lot like what we are and who we are.

07:29.698 --> 07:37.650
Yet God promises comfort, redemption, and words of Isaiah, a bare-armed revelation.

07:41.602 --> 07:45.066
It's not like God is like rolling up his sleeves for a fight.

07:45.126 --> 07:52.775
It's more for a rescue, like a father bearing his arm to lift his child out of danger.

07:57.080 --> 08:01.545
And it's not just for a few, but it's for all.

08:01.785 --> 08:03.907
It's for all nations, for all the earth to see.

08:03.927 --> 08:06.590
And that's part of our job.

08:08.493 --> 08:09.714
That's what Christmas is.

08:11.074 --> 08:16.063
The baby in a manger is God's holy arm laid bare.

08:18.027 --> 08:19.229
The word made flesh.

08:21.113 --> 08:34.418
The glory that we can see, we can touch, we can hold, not an overwhelming fire, not in danger, but in a human life that's full of grace and truth and love.

08:37.442 --> 08:40.805
And John contrasts all of this with the law given through Moses.

08:40.865 --> 08:41.606
The law is good.

08:41.646 --> 08:45.850
It shows us God's willingness and remember our confirmation.

08:45.870 --> 08:49.213
It shows our sin, but we know it can't save us.

08:50.234 --> 08:52.316
It diagnoses us for sure.

08:52.336 --> 08:59.663
It tells us what we probably already know about ourselves, but that's a conviction that the law does.

09:01.865 --> 09:06.930
But the grace, the truth, the balm, the cure comes through Jesus Christ.

09:08.450 --> 09:13.518
Out of his fullness, we've received grace and grace of grace already given.

09:16.543 --> 09:20.709
Wave upon wave of undeserved favor.

09:23.013 --> 09:33.970
This little baby, this infant that will need human nurturing and protection, as we'll see next week, next Sunday, is the fullness of God.

09:37.986 --> 09:49.499
And as we think about our own lives, we can kind of use that little example of Jerusalem, that Isaiah paints, but maybe this Christmas finds you or us joyful.

09:50.741 --> 09:54.405
Maybe we're surrounded by family and friends and laughter.

09:57.168 --> 10:05.938
But maybe for some of us, it's tinged with a little bit of sadness or sorrow or something that's weighing on us that we can't seem to shake.

10:08.610 --> 10:11.453
Maybe it's an empty chair at your table.

10:11.513 --> 10:18.380
Maybe it's a strained family relationship or the weight of another year's regrets.

10:21.263 --> 10:29.352
And it seems that that law and our conscience seems to always be whispering to us and planting seeds of doubt.

10:32.896 --> 10:35.058
Happens to me and I know it happens to you.

10:38.178 --> 10:38.839
It's the sin.

10:39.139 --> 10:42.743
The whisper is, you've fallen short.

10:43.184 --> 10:44.245
You've got to take control.

10:44.305 --> 10:46.587
You need to turn things around.

10:46.628 --> 10:49.871
But as Christians, we hear the gospel.

10:50.812 --> 10:52.474
We hear what the message is this morning.

10:52.494 --> 10:55.097
The word became flesh for you.

10:56.138 --> 10:59.262
He dwelt among us to share our joys and pains.

10:59.322 --> 11:00.523
He was born in poverty.

11:00.583 --> 11:06.610
He faced rejection and ultimately died on a cross to redeem you.

11:09.314 --> 11:13.960
And as Isaiah foretold in his prophecies, his salvation is visible to all.

11:14.240 --> 11:15.402
It's not hidden away.

11:15.442 --> 11:19.747
It's not you need some special code or special handshake to get into it.

11:19.887 --> 11:21.049
It's for all.

11:23.372 --> 11:28.438
Nailed to the wood, risen from the tomb, ascended to heaven for all.

11:31.642 --> 11:32.944
No one has ever seen God.

11:33.004 --> 11:37.970
John reminds us, but Jesus, the son.

11:38.210 --> 11:40.794
who is God himself has made himself known.

11:43.118 --> 11:48.566
We heard it in our children's Christmas play, not in carnation, in carnation.

11:51.010 --> 11:53.894
In Jesus, we see the humanity of God.

11:53.934 --> 11:59.523
We see the Father's heart not distant and angry, but close and compassionate.

12:00.985 --> 12:04.370
We see an assurance of how our story ends.

12:07.074 --> 12:18.031
If you were here last night, Pastor Midau preached a great sermon and he used an example of a testimony that U.S.

12:18.051 --> 12:19.774
Senator Ben Sossi wrote.

12:20.034 --> 12:22.558
And I was up there and I said, I was gonna use that one.

12:24.642 --> 12:35.058
But I think it bears repeating because when I look at the testimony, the conviction of faith that he gave in this moment,

12:35.906 --> 12:43.719
I think it's a good example for us as well to ask ourselves, would that be my reaction?

12:45.582 --> 12:55.639
So I'm going to read it, and I want to emphasize one other part that I'd like to draw a little close attention to.

12:55.699 --> 12:57.922
Former U.S.

12:57.942 --> 13:02.610
Senator Ben-Sasi of Nebraska announced on Tuesday that he has been diagnosed with

13:02.754 --> 13:07.820
mestatastic stage four pancreatic cancer, calling it a death sentence.

13:07.840 --> 13:14.148
And he said, this is a tough note to write, but since a bunch of you have started to suspect something, I'll cut to the chase.

13:15.010 --> 13:18.374
Last week, I was diagnosed with stage four pancreatic cancer.

13:18.995 --> 13:21.338
Advanced pancreatic cancer is nasty stuff.

13:21.358 --> 13:22.279
It's a death sentence.

13:23.300 --> 13:27.285
But I already had a death sentence before last week.

13:27.305 --> 13:27.986
We all do.

13:29.858 --> 13:34.043
Sassy was just 53 years old, noted, I've got less time than I would prefer.

13:36.506 --> 13:41.252
But he also expressed his Christian hope, noting that he is a Christian.

13:43.756 --> 13:51.285
And he says, as a Christian, the weeks running up the Christmas are a time to orient our hearts toward the hope of what's to come.

13:53.288 --> 13:58.194
Not an abstract hope in fanciful human goodness, not hope in

13:58.434 --> 14:04.521
a vague, hallmark, sappy spirituality, not a bootstrapped hope in our own strength.

14:06.763 --> 14:08.225
Nope.

14:08.245 --> 14:12.250
Often we lazily say hope when what we mean is optimism.

14:13.931 --> 14:19.418
But to be clear, optimism is great and it's absolutely necessary, but it's insufficient.

14:20.879 --> 14:26.866
It's not the kind of thing that holds up when you tell your daughters you're not going to walk them down the aisle.

14:27.394 --> 14:31.498
nor telling your mom and pops that they're gonna bury their son, he noted.

14:35.842 --> 14:51.957
And this is the kernel that I love, that he speaks in the last sentence, and he writes, those who know ourselves to need a physician should dang well look forward to enduring beauty and eventual fulfillment.

14:54.180 --> 14:56.722
That is, we hope, in a real deliverer,

14:57.762 --> 15:03.671
a rescuing God born at a real time in a real place.

15:05.794 --> 15:11.402
But the eternal city with foundations and without cancer is not yet.

15:15.628 --> 15:27.506
And that is the message that we hear this morning that God came down to us incarnate as a human that we recognize

15:28.418 --> 15:30.201
that we can see, that we can relate to.

15:33.045 --> 15:36.070
And that's the invitation to us for this Christmas.

15:38.674 --> 15:56.242
As Isaiah says, we burst into songs of joy, not because our lives are perfect, not because we can do it all ourselves, not because we may have a

15:56.546 --> 16:11.610
medical condition, we may have a family situation, we may have a relationship that is in need of God's grace, but we burst into songs of joy because God has came down to comfort us.

16:13.693 --> 16:24.050
The ruins of our lives and the ruins of that sin has caused in our lives are redeemed in Christ, not of our doing.

16:26.114 --> 16:33.722
His glory, full of grace and truth, isn't in the distance.

16:35.384 --> 16:39.268
It's not some like distant echo we hear in a cave or something.

16:40.309 --> 16:40.789
It's here.

16:43.012 --> 16:44.754
It's here where he said he was going to be.

16:46.175 --> 16:47.276
It's here in the Word.

16:47.356 --> 16:48.678
It's here in our sacrament.

16:49.238 --> 16:50.760
It's where two or three are gathered.

16:50.880 --> 16:52.882
He promises he will be with us.

16:57.474 --> 16:59.076
And we share those things here.

17:00.358 --> 17:15.556
We share those things as we gather, share those things at this table, uniting us and Christians who have gone before us and brothers and sisters of faith from this congregation from your family that are before us are right here with us in the church triumphant.

17:18.580 --> 17:24.707
And we cherish this salvation by grace alone through faith alone and Christ alone.

17:25.729 --> 17:26.930
No works required.

17:28.066 --> 17:32.892
No pulling ourselves up by the bootstraps, just receiving the gift.

17:36.877 --> 17:46.188
And I guess this means for us today that we need to be cognizant and constantly aware of the word that has come down for us.

17:47.109 --> 17:54.098
And if we're carrying burdens, if we're carrying stress and strife in our life, we lay them in the manger.

17:56.610 --> 18:05.240
And if you're rejoicing and your heart is full of joy and you need to share that joy with someone who's maybe not experiencing that.

18:07.402 --> 18:14.690
And remember that you are carrying the light of Christ and that salvation is for all, for all the earth.

18:17.633 --> 18:21.938
And I guess as we leave this place today and we

18:22.114 --> 18:27.540
continue the celebrations, whether they're with a few of us or with a large family gathering.

18:28.741 --> 18:42.415
We carry that light of Christ into our world, to where we live, to our people, making God's glory known to all in the name of the Father and of the Son and the Holy Spirit.

18:43.416 --> 18:43.757
Amen.

18:44.698 --> 18:48.722
Now, may the peace of God with guards your hearts and minds

18:49.314 --> 18:52.089
Let Christ Jesus dwell in you this day and always.

18:52.391 --> 18:57.298
Amen.

